---
title: Installing Flo
---

This topic provides instructions for installing Flo for Spring XD.

1. Install or update to Spring XD 1.2 GA.

1. Visit the [Flo product page](https://network.pivotal.io/products/p-spring-flo) and download `flo-spring-xd-admin-ui-client-1.2.0.RELEASE.zip`.

1. Navigate to XD_HOME/lib directory and unzip `flo-spring-xd-admin-ui-client-1.2.0.RELEASE.zip` to replace the existing `spring-xd-admin-ui-client-1.2.0.RELEASE.jar`.

1. Clear your browser cache.

1. Access Flo for Spring XD at the following URI endpoints:
	* Main dashboard: `http://HOST_NAME:PORT/admin-ui`
	* Flo canvas: `http://HOST_NAME:PORT/admin-ui/#/streams/create`
	* Health monitoring: `http://HOST_NAME:PORT/admin-ui/#/streams/definitions`
	* Metrics are located at: `http://HOST_NAME:PORT/admin-ui/#/streams/definitions` 

<p class='note'><strong>Note</strong>: You must enable JMX in your Spring XD cluster. By default it is disabled.</p>